XLV. 1 To examine the whole matter, we must remark that true religion, common to all ages, rests mainly on four principles3 of which the first is, that God exists‚ and is one: the second, that God is not any visible object, but something higher: the third, that God cares for human affairs, and judges them with perfect justice: the fourth, that God is the creator of all other things. These four points arc delivered in the first four commandments of the Decalogue.
